DCPS will continue to monitor enrollment and boundary changes are expected to right size the enrollment with the building capacity.  It should be noted that the full impact of the boundary changes will not be felt until the boundary changes have been in place for a few years.  DCPS feels that the reported capacity may be low because of how Wilson uses their classrooms.  DCPS typically assumes that classrooms are used 80% of the time at the High School level, but because Wilson utilizes a “floating teacher” methodology, it is believed their classrooms are utilized closer to 85% of the time.
